<div class="panel panel-primary col-lg-12">
  <div class="panel-heading text-center text-uppercase" style="height:50px; font-size:large"><a style="text-decoration:none; color:White">Outage Recovery Plan</a></div>
  <div class="panel-body">
             <p>
             In the hours before, during and after disaster, Meralco follows a well-rehearsed disaster plan procedure to reduce the customer outage duration.
             </p>
                <br/>

    <div class="panel panel-primary col-lg-6">
        <div class="panel-heading">
            <h3 class="panel-title text-center">We are ready once the storm hits</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
               <ul> 
              <li>Meralco crews are cross-trained in storm response tasks and prepared to turn from their regular jobs to help restore power. </li>
              <li>Specially trained workers, who routinely are not in the field, are reassigned to locate and monitor downed wire to ensure public safety.</li>
              <li>Standby plans  and  additional crew in place to repair damage to LV service lines.</li>
              <li>Additional resource plan is in place to support customer call center to help handle the expected high volume of customer call</li>
              <br />
              <br />
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel panel-primary col-lg-6">
        <div class="panel-heading ">
            <h3 class="panel-title text-center">Activities  from Centralized Storm Centre</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
             <ul>
               <li>Repair crews are managed and dispatched, including those not normally assigned to the storm-damaged area.</li>
               <li>Local officials are notified of any specific problems in their province or cities etc.</li>
               <li>Contractors and neighboring utility are given safety briefings and clearly assigned the expected repair works.</li>
               <li>The  news media are kept updated on damage reports, restoration progress and safety advisories.</li>
               <li>Following every major storm event, a detailed ‘lessons-learned’ meeting is conducted and, as necessary, Disaster Plan procedures are further improved.</li>
             </ul>
        </div>
    </div>


  </div>
</div>
